wikipedia_page.main: Ella Du Cane (1874-1943) was a British artist best known for her watercolors of landscapes and exotic locales.

response: *Ella Du Cane - British Artist who visited in 1904

Du Cane's tenure in Tasmania saw the colony grow strong and prosperous, partly due to industrial and resources booms and the improvement of communication between Tasmania, the mainland and England. He left Hobart in November 1874, and was appointed KCMG the next year after his return to England. Du Cane died at his family estate in Braxted Park, Essex on 25 February 1889,Rimmer, Gordon. 'Du Cane, Sir Charles (1825–1889)', Australian Dictionary of Biography, Volume 4, Melbourne University Press, 1972, pp 106–107. survived by five children, including the artist Ella Du Cane.
